\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 A bare, twenty foot by twenty foot chamber appears occupied by more goblins. Two small doors line the east wall and rope tied to the furthest doors handle is held at the other end by a goblin barking orders at the others. Only a dice covered table and rickety chairs decorate the place while the walls may have once had frescoes upon them but are fair too faded to make out.
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 Two warriors in this chamber are likely to join any battle in area 1, while the remaining goblins hold up here protecting to the door to room 9. The acolyte is holding the rope that with a sharp tug opens the door to area 8a, which confines the zombie. He will hold off pulling the rope until the party have engaged and are closer to the door than he is as the zombie will attack the living soul nearest to it. He will then bang on the door to 9 and run inside, looking for aid from the goblins there. The small in the south east is being used as a toilet and stinks unbearable.\'a0
